1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:03,726
TextSink. Four voices. One truth.

2
00:00:03,726 --> 00:00:07,833
Built on Gemma 4 and Fireworks AI, for the

3
00:00:07,833 --> 00:00:10,179
AMD Developer Hackathon.

4
00:00:11,300 --> 00:00:14,852
One video. Four voices. A formal narrator, a deadpan

5
00:00:14,852 --> 00:00:18,610
cynic, a developer who's seen things, and your favorite

6
00:00:18,610 --> 00:00:22,435
neighbor. This is TextSink. And every word you're seeing

7
00:00:22,435 --> 00:00:25,510
was written live by Gemma 4, about the actual

8
00:00:25,510 --> 00:00:26,739
competition clips.

9
00:00:27,440 --> 00:00:30,958
Under the hood, it's the official Track 2 contract.

10
00:00:30,958 --> 00:00:33,993
Tasks in, captions out, fully containerized.

11
00:00:33,993 --> 00:00:37,926
The container probes its model access, grounds every clip

12
00:00:37,926 --> 00:00:41,720
in scene facts, drafts three captions per style, judges

13
00:00:41,720 --> 00:00:44,273
its own drafts, and ships the winner.

14
00:00:44,273 --> 00:00:47,722
And if grounding ever comes back empty, it refuses

15
00:00:47,722 --> 00:00:52,000
to caption blind. An empty caption is structurally impossible.

16
00:00:52,706 --> 00:00:55,777
Four styles isn't one prompt with four adjectives.

17
00:00:55,777 --> 00:00:58,909
Broadcast precision. Deadpan, scale mismatch irony.

18
00:00:58,909 --> 00:01:02,472
A developer culture metaphor built from what's actually on

19
00:01:02,472 --> 00:01:04,928
screen. And warm, everyday relatability.

20
00:01:04,928 --> 00:01:06,955
An AI judge can blind sort these.

21
00:01:06,955 --> 00:01:08,306
That's the tone score.

22
00:01:09,006 --> 00:01:12,510
Then we kept going. The same grounding becomes real

23
00:01:12,510 --> 00:01:16,289
closed captions. A timed subtitle track you can toggle,

24
00:01:16,289 --> 00:01:19,587
with one consistent voice across the whole clip.

25
00:01:19,587 --> 00:01:23,641
A tiny orange predator prepares for total world domination.

26
00:01:23,641 --> 00:01:25,359
The menace is closing in.

27
00:01:25,359 --> 00:01:26,046
Send help.

28
00:01:26,746 --> 00:01:30,125
And because one voice is a monologue: The Hecklers.

29
00:01:30,125 --> 00:01:33,769
Two different models, Gemma 4 versus GPT-OSS, watch the

30
00:01:33,769 --> 00:01:36,287
clip and argue about it, turn by turn.

31
00:01:36,287 --> 00:01:40,660
Every line generated live. It's a strawberry milkshake apocalypse,

32
00:01:40,660 --> 00:01:44,503
Gus! Apocalypse? It's just sunset, not your dairy fantasy.

33
00:01:44,503 --> 00:01:47,683
And when the code reviewer meets the vibe coder:

34
00:01:47,683 --> 00:01:50,731
touch grass, Lint, before your soul segfaults.

35
00:01:50,731 --> 00:01:52,586
The models wrote every word.

36
00:01:53,313 --> 00:01:55,366
Gemma grounds it. Writes it.

37
00:01:55,366 --> 00:01:58,886
Argues it. Judges it. And last night, it trained

38
00:01:58,886 --> 00:02:02,333
its own captioner on the drafts it judged best.

39
00:02:02,333 --> 00:02:04,753
TextSink. Four voices. One truth.

40
00:02:05,753 --> 00:02:11,475
TextSink. Thanks to AMD, Fireworks AI, Google DeepMind's Gemma,

41
00:02:11,475 --> 00:02:14,473
and lablab.ai. Find us on GitHub.
